column5: Lots of choices this weekend to see and do...Spring Fishing Show in Mississauga..Daytona 500 (which Greg Biffle or Jeff Gordon will win!)..BASS Classic from New Orleans, LA..(which will be shown at the Fishing Show btw..)hard to pick a winner on this one!  whats everyone doing besides their 'honey do list' on a weekend like this coming up?
I'll be working 10 hours per day just Like I've been doing for the past two weeks.

Ill be golfing friday at an indoor place for a "work bonding time". Sat and/or sunday ill be at the fishing show checkin out the goodies, seeing some friends and working a booth or 2. Monday... Maybe ill go fishing! Lol
I'll be searching for some new fishing buddies that aren't effected with that "can't go" virus called work!
I'll be in Ottawa for the long weekend, but I heard that the fishing show would have a "spots bar" type of set-up this year, mainly to show the 500 I think.

I will be working on making baits here at home but taking Friday night off for the truck race Saturday night off for the Nationwide race and Sunday afternoon off for the Cup race. Depending on how they go I might just be back here working again or if I can find them on line I will listen and watch whale making baits.

Free to do whatever I want all weekend, like every weekend but I won't be partaking in any of the events mentioned.  Likely be building rods and downing a few cold ones, ya know.....cork dust is pretty dry.

Come on spiel, you can go to the fishing show on saturday. i will bring a 4 wheel dolly and push you up and down the isle's. then when we meet up with roy, we can put him on the dolly and go bowling!!!!!
ROY ACTUALLY TOLD YOU ABOUT HIS DOLLY ? Wow !!!He must really like you
